<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-09"><hi rend="italic">August 9,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p rend="center">[Received August 14, 1900, through Chinese legation.
                                Date of sending lost in transmission.]</p>
                            <p>(Mr. Conger reports that they are being fired upon daily by Imperial
                                troops. Their losses are 60 killed and 120 wounded. Have reached
                                half portion of horse flesh, and have food for only a fortnight. Six
                                children have died and many others are sick.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>